    public static class Short2FloatMaps.Singleton
extends Short2FloatFunctions.Singleton
implements Short2FloatMap, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    An immutable class representing a type-specific singleton map.

    This class may be useful to implement your own in case you subclass a type-specific map.

      • short2FloatEntrySet

        public ObjectSet<Short2FloatMap.Entry> short2FloatEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Short2FloatMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Short2FloatMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        short2FloatEntrySet in interface Short2FloatMap
        Returns:
        a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        Map.entrySet()
